        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-19T14:53:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The long parameter list doesn\u0027t seem like a big issue to me since you have to type all the params anyway either in one function together or in two functions called one after the other. And we only do this in one place.\n\nSo yeah I\u0027d go either to a combined GrD3DPipelineState::Make call or move all the creation of the ID3D12PipelineState to the builder, which I don\u0027t think even needs to be a static member of the class. Couldn\u0027t it just be a static helper in the cpp?",
